00:21:29,960 --> 00:21:34,480
Seems like you two are quite close, aren’t you?

256
00:21:35,440 --> 00:21:37,440
Because last night I noticed that.

257
00:21:37,440 --> 00:21:39,080
He was really worried about you.

258
00:21:40,800 --> 00:21:42,360
Not that close.

259
00:21:42,960 --> 00:21:45,680
He just likes to annoy me and get on my nerve.

260
00:21:48,040 --> 00:21:49,280
Go on and finish your food.

261
00:21:49,480 --> 00:21:50,440
Then I’ll drop you off.

262
00:21:52,960 --> 00:21:53,560
What!

263
00:21:55,080 --> 00:21:56,720
Drop me off? Do I have to go somewhere?

264
00:21:56,880 --> 00:21:59,960
Did you forget that you have to fly to Nongkai today?

265
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:01,360
Oh, that’s right!

266
00:22:02,440 --> 00:22:04,840
If you hadn’t remind me then I’d have missed the flight for sure.

267
00:22:04,840 --> 00:22:06,080
Go pack your things then.

268
00:22:06,680 --> 00:22:07,520
Yai!

269
00:22:09,720 --> 00:22:11,040
Wake up right now!

270
00:22:11,040 --> 00:22:12,960
Did you forget that you have to go to Nongkai?

271
00:22:15,440 --> 00:22:19,600
Nongkai.

272
00:23:04,160 --> 00:23:05,120
Look at her.

273
00:23:06,600 --> 00:23:09,200
She was giving me all ears while we were on the plane.

274
00:23:09,320 --> 00:23:11,360
She’s still mad with me.

275
00:23:11,840 --> 00:23:12,920
So, my dear brother.

276
00:23:13,360 --> 00:23:14,680
Help me make up with her.

277
00:23:15,120 --> 00:23:18,720
Or else I’d be cleaning the toilet at home during the festival this evening.

278
00:23:20,960 --> 00:23:22,200
Seriously…

279
00:23:22,640 --> 00:23:26,120
Sand isn’t that kind of girl. She’ll forgive you soon enough.

280
00:23:26,120 --> 00:23:27,800
Before you said that...

281
00:23:28,240 --> 00:23:29,360
make sure you look at her face first.

282
00:23:39,280 --> 00:23:40,640
She’s gorgeous.

283
00:23:42,240 --> 00:23:47,560
I know that. But she’s also very scary. I’m afraid of her.

284
00:23:47,560 --> 00:23:48,960
Are you guys talking about me?

285
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:51,320
Of course, not.

286
00:23:51,800 --> 00:23:54,200
He was telling me how nice you are.

287
00:23:54,600 --> 00:23:57,040
And that you look really beautiful today.

288
00:23:57,920 --> 00:24:00,240
But you’d look even more beautiful...

289
00:24:00,240 --> 00:24:02,320
if you stop being mad at him.

290
00:24:02,320 --> 00:24:04,960
Incredibly beautiful, my baby.

291
00:24:04,960 --> 00:24:06,960
Do you want some water? The weathe is quite hot.

292
00:24:06,960 --> 00:24:09,080
But you look even hotter.

293
00:24:09,560 --> 00:24:11,320
Tonight at the festival...

294
00:24:11,320 --> 00:24:13,280
should we go try something delicious?

295
00:24:13,280 --> 00:24:13,600
Okay.

296
00:24:13,600 --> 00:24:15,520
Like Spicy Papaya Salad...

297
00:24:15,880 --> 00:24:19,480
And grilled river fish with chilled beer.

298
00:24:20,720 --> 00:24:22,160
My mouth is watering just by thinking of them.

299
00:24:22,280 --> 00:24:23,400
How would you like that, honey?

300
00:24:23,400 --> 00:24:26,040
Yes, I really love chilled beer.

301
00:24:26,200 --> 00:24:30,040
Those are all your favourites, huh?

302
00:24:30,520 --> 00:24:32,040
I still haven’t lectured you about last night.

303
00:24:32,040 --> 00:24:35,640
That you got so drunk and almost made us both miss the plane.

304
00:24:36,720 --> 00:24:38,560
Oh, so you remembered? Why didn’t you tell me then?

305
00:24:38,560 --> 00:24:40,760
Are you blaming me now?

306
00:24:41,320 --> 00:24:42,240
Is it my fault?

307
00:24:42,240 --> 00:24:45,800
What? Of course, not, sweetie.

308
00:24:45,800 --> 00:24:49,880
I was just kidding. Please forgive me. It’s all my fault.

309
00:24:49,880 --> 00:24:54,280
It’s my fault. Please tell me what you want me to do tonight, my baby.

310
00:24:54,280 --> 00:24:56,000
Please behave. We’re at the temple.

311
00:24:56,000 --> 00:24:57,600
Let’s go see the Abbot.

312
00:24:59,800 --> 00:25:02,360
Honey, wait for me too. Don’t you want some water?

313
00:25:02,360 --> 00:25:04,360
I bought it from over there.

314
00:25:06,160 --> 00:25:08,720
Isn’t she adorable? That’s my wife.

315
00:25:10,000 --> 00:25:11,560
Goodmorning, Luangpor.

316
00:25:11,560 --> 00:25:13,600
Morning.

317
00:25:14,960 --> 00:25:19,360
Come a little closer. I’m happy for you two.

318
00:25:19,960 --> 00:25:25,200
You’re now on the special investigation team just like what you’ve wanted to.

319
00:25:25,760 --> 00:25:28,720
It’s all because of you, Luangpor,

320
00:25:28,720 --> 00:25:30,560
that we could finally did it.

321
00:25:30,800 --> 00:25:33,520
You’ve always taken a great care of us.

322
00:25:33,520 --> 00:25:34,680
We are who we are because of you.

323
00:25:35,440 --> 00:25:37,560
We are so grateful to you.

324
00:25:39,720 --> 00:25:44,200
You did it because you already have it in you.

325
00:25:44,840 --> 00:25:47,480
Please take a good care of yourself from now on.

326
00:25:47,920 --> 00:25:50,120
Be mindful in everything you do.

327
00:25:51,200 --> 00:25:53,040
Never lose your awareness.

328
00:25:53,520 --> 00:25:54,560
Always be calm.

329
00:25:55,160 --> 00:25:56,160
Don’t be a hotheaded.

330
00:25:57,480 --> 00:26:00,280
As long as he has me with him, I’ll always make sure he behaves.

331
00:26:02,080 --> 00:26:03,280
I’ll always make sure he behaves.

332
00:26:03,280 --> 00:26:05,280
You can rest assured that he’ll always be mindful.

333
00:26:07,400 --> 00:26:10,400
Maybe you should tell that to yourself first.

334
00:26:11,200 --> 00:26:14,280
Whenever they are together, there’s always trouble.

335
00:26:15,240 --> 00:26:16,360
I agree.

336
00:26:16,600 --> 00:26:18,080
Totally agree.

337
00:26:18,760 --> 00:26:21,040
Without you...

338
00:26:21,640 --> 00:26:24,360
harn would surely be more calm and always think twice.

339
00:26:24,760 --> 00:26:27,320
You are quick-tempered and act on impluse.

340
00:26:27,320 --> 00:26:30,080
Please mercy me.

341
00:26:30,560 --> 00:26:32,800
Darling, I got scolded again.

342
00:26:32,800 --> 00:26:33,240
There you go.

343
00:26:33,240 --> 00:26:35,840
Ouch! It really hurts, babe.

344
00:26:35,840 --> 00:26:36,880
Does it?

345
00:26:36,880 --> 00:26:37,680
Does it hurt a lot?

346
00:26:37,680 --> 00:26:38,760
Ouch!….

347
00:26:39,680 --> 00:26:41,240
Go that way.

348
00:26:41,920 --> 00:26:44,920
While you’re staying here.

349
00:26:45,240 --> 00:26:47,200
Let me warn you about something

350
00:26:48,000 --> 00:26:52,280
Make sure you often meditate and dedicate the merits to those whom you have wronged in the past.

351
00:26:53,560 --> 00:26:57,280
So that it would help lighten the consequences of your karma.

352
00:26:57,320 --> 00:26:58,360
Got it?

353
00:27:02,640 --> 00:27:05,200
Is he still not free from them?

354
00:27:05,480 --> 00:27:07,160
They’ve been after him since when he was born.

355
00:27:07,520 --> 00:27:09,320
That’s why he had to live at the temple.

356
00:27:09,840 --> 00:27:13,040
What do they want from him? Why are they so vengeful?

357
00:27:39,080 --> 00:27:41,920
Are you going to Rocket Festival tonight?

358
00:27:42,680 --> 00:27:44,840
Absolutely. They won’t miss the chance.

359
00:27:45,920 --> 00:27:48,280
Do you want to go home to visit your grandma first?

360
00:27:48,400 --> 00:27:50,440
We can meet again this evening.

361
00:27:51,800 --> 00:27:53,840
’m going to stay here tonight.

362
00:27:54,000 --> 00:27:56,640
So that I can help take care of the Abbot.

363
00:27:57,280 --> 00:27:59,280
You and Yai go back first.

364
00:27:59,600 --> 00:28:00,720
I’ll give you a call later.

365
00:28:01,040 --> 00:28:01,880
Okay.

366
00:28:03,160 --> 00:28:05,440
We’d get going then. Goodbye, Luangpor.

367
00:28:05,440 --> 00:28:07,680
Stay safe, both of you.

368
00:28:15,920 --> 00:28:20,000
Tharn, can you do me a favour?

369
00:28:21,320 --> 00:28:22,320
Luangpor,

370
00:28:22,920 --> 00:28:25,520
Why do you ask me to bring an extra set of bedding?

371
00:28:25,760 --> 00:28:28,040
Someone will also sleep here tonight.

372
00:28:28,560 --> 00:28:31,880
Go and make your bed in the pavillioin first.

373
00:28:31,880 --> 00:28:33,040
Okay.

374
00:28:38,000 --> 00:28:39,920
Phaya!

375
00:28:41,240 --> 00:28:43,160
Tharn!

376
00:28:44,080 --> 00:28:45,120
What on earth are you doing here?

377
00:28:54,920 --> 00:28:57,680
Goodevening, Luangpor. Do you remember me?

378
00:28:58,600 --> 00:29:02,480
Oh, I haven’t seen you for a long time. How are you?

379
00:29:03,200 --> 00:29:04,240
I’m good.

380
00:29:04,640 --> 00:29:08,720
You two spent a lot of time together during the training, didn’t you recognised each other?

381
00:29:11,640 --> 00:29:14,880
Do you mean, Phaya and I...

382
00:29:15,200 --> 00:29:17,720
have met before we went to the training camp?

383
00:29:18,400 --> 00:29:19,800
That’s right.

384
00:29:20,040 --> 00:29:25,800
You used to give him the amulet when he was young.

385
00:29:26,040 --> 00:29:26,920
What?

386
00:29:30,160 --> 00:29:32,320
You’re that boy who gave me the amulet?

387
00:29:50,480 --> 00:29:52,840
Thank you so much, Luangpor.

388
00:29:53,520 --> 00:29:57,320
For always taking care of Tharn since the day he lost his parents in an accident.

389
00:29:57,520 --> 00:29:59,400
You and this temple...

390
00:29:59,400 --> 00:30:01,760
have always been a sanctuary for Tharn and I.

391
00:30:04,920 --> 00:30:10,080
He often told me that all he has is his grandmother.

392
00:30:10,480 --> 00:30:13,640
So, he doesn’t want anything bad to happen to you.

393
00:30:14,160 --> 00:30:16,560
That’s why he asked if he could live here.

394
00:30:19,560 --> 00:30:22,680
I don’t want him to blame himself.

395
00:30:23,600 --> 00:30:24,960
I could only hope that...

396
00:30:25,200 --> 00:30:30,000
he will eventually forget about that terrible accident when he gets older.

397
00:30:31,120 --> 00:30:34,080
Everything has already been destined.

398
00:30:34,800 --> 00:30:38,480
His life is written by the karma he did in his past life.

399
00:30:40,320 --> 00:30:42,400
Is there a way to fix it?

400
00:30:45,920 --> 00:30:47,200
Well, there is somehow.

401
00:30:48,280 --> 00:30:55,600
His destiny has been entwined with someone since his past life.

402
00:30:56,160 --> 00:31:00,480
That person will lead him to experience bad things.

403
00:31:01,720 --> 00:31:07,520
But it is also that person who would be able to free him from his karma.

404
00:31:30,520 --> 00:31:32,320
Tharn, let’s go to the festival.

405
00:31:34,240 --> 00:31:40,360
Tharn, it’s the 15th day of the 11th waxing moon today. Are you going to the Rocket Festival with Yai?

406
00:31:40,560 --> 00:31:41,640
Yes, grandma.

407
00:31:41,920 --> 00:31:43,520
Please don’t worry.

408
00:31:43,520 --> 00:31:45,200
I’ll take a good care of myself.

409
00:31:45,200 --> 00:31:47,680
When the festival is done, I’ll go visit you at home.

410
00:31:49,680 --> 00:31:50,920
Take care of each other, okay?

411
00:31:50,920 --> 00:31:51,520
Yes, grandma.

412
00:31:52,680 --> 00:31:54,040
- Let's help pack up
- Okay.

413
00:31:56,480 --> 00:32:01,480
Tharn, I need a little favour from you.

414
00:32:03,080 --> 00:32:08,480
Make sure you track down the owner of this amulet by tonight.

415
00:32:09,560 --> 00:32:12,440
Once you’ve found him, give him this amulet.

416
00:32:16,760 --> 00:32:20,640
Who is the owner of this amulet, Luangpor?

417
00:32:21,640 --> 00:32:25,880
If you meet him, your feelings will tell you.

418
00:32:25,880 --> 00:32:28,080
Who is the owner of this necklace?

419
00:32:28,520 --> 00:32:30,760
But you must find him.

420
00:32:31,280 --> 00:32:35,080
Whether you’d be free from those whom you have wronged in the past...

421
00:32:35,880 --> 00:32:41,560
depends on whether you’d be able to find the owner of this amulet tonight.

422
00:32:48,760 --> 00:32:49,920
Let’s go.

423
00:32:50,560 --> 00:32:51,720
Goodbye, Luangpor.

424
00:32:55,480 --> 00:32:59,640
Tharn! Yai! Come quick! What took you so long? I’ve been here for a while.

425
00:33:00,240 --> 00:33:01,560
Let’s go.

426
00:33:19,120 --> 00:33:22,240
Who are you looking for?

427
00:33:22,600 --> 00:33:25,640
The person that the Abbot asked me to give this amulet to.

428
00:33:26,640 --> 00:33:30,400
Geez, I thought you and I could just have fun at the festival.

429
00:33:30,680 --> 00:33:34,240
Too bad the Abbot also gave you a mission for tonight.

430
00:33:34,880 --> 00:33:36,160
Now, I’m bored.

431
00:33:36,880 --> 00:33:41,840
The Abbot said there’ll be a sign and I’ll know once I see him.

432
00:33:42,080 --> 00:33:43,960
The owner of this amulet.

433
00:33:43,960 --> 00:33:45,760
What sign?

434
00:33:45,760 --> 00:33:47,560
What are you two talking about?

435
00:33:48,240 --> 00:33:50,160
Some nonsese stuff.

436
00:33:51,880 --> 00:33:54,080
Let’s light up these firecrackers. I bought tons of them.

437
00:33:54,080 --> 00:33:57,640
After we finish eating, let’s go watch something at the outdoor cinema.

438
00:33:57,720 --> 00:33:58,760
Yeah, let’s do that.

439
00:33:58,760 --> 00:34:00,240
- You take the meatballs to eat first.
- Okay

440
00:34:00,920 --> 00:34:02,640
What’s this for?

441
00:34:04,560 --> 00:34:07,720
Help! Help! My nephew is drowning!

442
00:34:09,840 --> 00:34:12,040
Help! My nephew is drowning!

443
00:34:21,120 --> 00:34:23,960
Tharn, what’s wrong?

444
00:34:25,520 --> 00:34:27,679
I saw a boy drowning.

445
00:34:27,679 --> 00:34:29,840
Geez, nonsense.

446
00:34:29,840 --> 00:34:31,679
Are you going to tell me that you have a vision?

447
00:34:32,199 --> 00:34:33,320
But I really saw it.

448
00:34:33,320 --> 00:34:35,800
Nonsense. Let’s go watch a movie.

449
00:34:35,800 --> 00:34:37,760
Help! My nephew is drowning!

450
00:34:45,520 --> 00:34:49,199
Help! Help! My nephew is drowning!

451
00:34:49,199 --> 00:34:53,000
Help! My nephew! He is drowning!

452
00:35:07,760 --> 00:35:08,640
Phaya!

453
00:35:10,160 --> 00:35:11,360
Phaya!

454
00:35:16,880 --> 00:35:17,960
Phaya!

455
00:35:21,480 --> 00:35:22,360
Wake up

456
00:35:25,200 --> 00:35:27,040
- Wake up
- Phaya

