460
00:35:49,360 --> 00:35:50,000
Thank you

461
00:35:50,000 --> 00:35:52,520
It’s okay. You’re safe now.

462
00:36:12,160 --> 00:36:15,040
Here are your clothes. Let’s go and get changed.

463
00:36:15,040 --> 00:36:20,600
- Thank you all of you so much for saving his life.
- You’re welcome.

464
00:36:22,720 --> 00:36:23,680
Tharn.

465
00:36:24,160 --> 00:36:26,000
You should go and get changed too.

466
00:36:27,200 --> 00:36:28,560
We’d get going then.

467
00:36:28,760 --> 00:36:30,200
Goodbye.

468
00:36:42,560 --> 00:36:46,400
Without him, my nephew would have been dead.

469
00:36:46,400 --> 00:36:48,120
Thank you so much indeed.

470
00:36:48,120 --> 00:36:52,800
Oh, it’s all right. I was quite worried when I heard about it.

471
00:36:53,120 --> 00:36:55,760
But what a relief to know that they were all safe.

472
00:36:57,160 --> 00:36:59,960
It’s probably like what you said.

473
00:37:01,120 --> 00:37:04,400
Your nephew is a very fortunate boy.

474
00:37:04,400 --> 00:37:06,200
So, he would probably live for a very long time.

475
00:37:07,120 --> 00:37:09,240
But you have to be careful though.

476
00:37:10,480 --> 00:37:15,120
If both of your destiny are entwined like what I think...

477
00:37:16,520 --> 00:37:19,720
you would eventually find each other again.

478
00:37:24,160 --> 00:37:28,320
Please take this as a thank you gift for saving my nephew’s life.

479
00:37:29,000 --> 00:37:34,520
Thank you, ma’am. But my grandma and the Abbot have taught me to always help those who are in need.

480
00:37:34,560 --> 00:37:37,600
Hey, but you did something good so you should take it.

481
00:37:39,640 --> 00:37:41,120
I’ll take it then.

482
00:37:41,120 --> 00:37:41,920
Thank you.

483
00:37:41,920 --> 00:37:42,760
Ouch!

484
00:37:45,960 --> 00:37:50,800
Well, then...I’ll give it to the Abbot instead.

485
00:37:51,640 --> 00:37:57,160
I’d like to donate this money for the temple and those who live here.

486
00:37:57,160 --> 00:38:00,360
So that you could use it as an education fund of these kids.

487
00:38:04,400 --> 00:38:07,320
I'm so close to getting the money,The Abbot.

488
00:38:11,400 --> 00:38:14,480
Are you here for the Rocket Festival?

489
00:38:14,760 --> 00:38:18,240
You don’t look local though.

490
00:38:18,520 --> 00:38:20,160
We came from Bangkok.

491
00:38:20,360 --> 00:38:23,680
My nephew often dreamt about the Naga.

492
00:38:23,680 --> 00:38:25,800
So, he insisted that I must take him to the festival.

493
00:38:25,800 --> 00:38:27,880
He wants to witness it by himself.

494
00:38:27,920 --> 00:38:32,040
But I had no idea why he almost got drowned.

495
00:38:32,760 --> 00:38:35,360
He doesn’t know how to swim.

496
00:38:35,360 --> 00:38:37,880
But he still wants to go and play near the riverbank.

497
00:38:38,960 --> 00:38:44,880
Grandma, I really heard someone calling me there last night.

498
00:38:49,600 --> 00:38:50,680
I want to go home now.

499
00:38:54,000 --> 00:38:57,120
Well then, please excuse us.

500
00:38:57,960 --> 00:39:00,160
Thank you so much once again.

501
00:39:00,320 --> 00:39:03,000
For saving my nephew’s life.

502
00:39:03,960 --> 00:39:05,480
You’re welcome. Please travel safe.

503
00:39:05,480 --> 00:39:06,800
Thank you.

504
00:39:07,120 --> 00:39:08,800
Please take care.

505
00:39:09,560 --> 00:39:10,240
Okay.

506
00:39:11,360 --> 00:39:14,360
If you have a chance to visit here again in the future,

507
00:39:14,800 --> 00:39:16,760
I hope we’ll meet again.

508
00:39:17,440 --> 00:39:18,520
Thank you.

509
00:39:18,520 --> 00:39:20,280
Let’s say goodbye to the Abbot.

510
00:39:28,200 --> 00:39:29,880
Have a safe trip.

511
00:40:01,160 --> 00:40:02,360
Please wait!

512
00:40:09,600 --> 00:40:10,400
Here, take it.

