515
00:40:17,280 --> 00:40:19,480
to find the owner of this amulet.

516
00:40:20,440 --> 00:40:22,440
I think you’re that person.

517
00:40:23,800 --> 00:40:24,920
But I don’t want it.

518
00:40:26,920 --> 00:40:28,160
Take it.

519
00:40:29,480 --> 00:40:30,880
It will help protect you.

520
00:40:33,600 --> 00:40:36,040
Until we meet again.

521
00:41:00,120 --> 00:41:03,000
ou’re that boy I saved from getting drowned?

522
00:41:04,040 --> 00:41:04,960
Geez.

523
00:41:05,240 --> 00:41:06,600
I shouldn’t have done that.

524
00:41:06,800 --> 00:41:08,080
Then we wouldn’t have to see each other again.

525
00:41:08,720 --> 00:41:09,800
But I’m glad

526
00:41:10,400 --> 00:41:12,960
to know that you were the boy who saved my life.

527
00:41:14,160 --> 00:41:15,280
Why are you glad?

528
00:41:15,920 --> 00:41:18,360
Well, because...

529
00:41:18,920 --> 00:41:21,800
you might be the one who can help answer the questions I have about my dreams.

530
00:41:23,840 --> 00:41:27,120
What you saw wasn’t a dream.

531
00:41:27,760 --> 00:41:30,120
It was your karma

532
00:41:31,880 --> 00:41:33,920
Are you saying that...

533
00:41:34,400 --> 00:41:37,480
they are those whom I have wronged in my past life?

534
00:41:39,120 --> 00:41:42,720
That’s right. But they are not just yours.

535
00:41:47,560 --> 00:41:48,840
Why are you looking at me like that?

536
00:41:49,800 --> 00:41:52,080
Do you remember what I used to tell you?

537
00:41:53,160 --> 00:41:57,200
hat you must find the owner of that amulet.

538
00:41:57,760 --> 00:42:00,240
Once you’ve found him, you must protect him with your life.

539
00:42:00,760 --> 00:42:05,120
Because he could help free you from your karma.

540
00:42:05,320 --> 00:42:08,400
It’s all up to the owner of this amulet.

541
00:42:10,600 --> 00:42:11,800
All these years,

542
00:42:12,760 --> 00:42:14,920
I’ve been trying to find the meaning of my dreams.

543
00:42:17,080 --> 00:42:19,640
I want to know what exactly it was...

544
00:42:20,560 --> 00:42:21,800
that I saw when I was drowning.

545
00:42:41,320 --> 00:42:43,240
After that incident...

546
00:42:46,000 --> 00:42:48,280
on every 15th day of the 11th waxing moon,

547
00:42:49,200 --> 00:42:50,680
I’d always see those pictures in my dream.

548
00:42:53,560 --> 00:42:54,800
A pair of green eyes.

549
00:42:59,520 --> 00:43:02,440
These pictures became clearer and cleaer every time I saw them.

550
00:43:06,360 --> 00:43:10,640
From just a pair of green eyes to seeing the Naga?

551
00:43:11,840 --> 00:43:12,640
Yes.

552
00:43:13,440 --> 00:43:17,240
Have you ever seen any of them?

553
00:43:18,640 --> 00:43:19,560
No.

554
00:43:20,720 --> 00:43:23,040
I only saw it once when I was down there to rescue you.

555
00:43:25,800 --> 00:43:27,960
But those green eyes that I saw...

556
00:43:28,960 --> 00:43:32,960
might have been the Naga fireballs.

557
00:43:38,240 --> 00:43:41,200
Everything that happens to both of you...

558
00:43:41,400 --> 00:43:42,960
is a result of your karma.

559
00:43:44,400 --> 00:43:46,520
You’d only know the answer...

560
00:43:47,320 --> 00:43:52,840
through the act of meditation which will enlighten you and lead you to the truth.

561
00:43:53,440 --> 00:43:56,120
Your destiny have been entwined since your past lives

562
00:43:56,520 --> 00:43:58,360
มันผูกกันมาหลายภพ

563
00:44:01,200 --> 00:44:02,480
You both are destined to help each other

564
00:44:03,600 --> 00:44:04,760
Trust each other.

565
00:44:05,560 --> 00:44:10,280
Only then, you would be able to free yourself from your karma.

566
00:44:17,040 --> 00:44:19,640
Your kind hearts are your best weapon.

567
00:44:20,840 --> 00:44:22,920
And remember to always trust each other

568
00:44:24,680 --> 00:44:25,760
Help each other.

569
00:44:27,720 --> 00:44:31,040
And you both would live a happy life,

570
00:44:31,840 --> 00:44:33,880
like you’ve always dreamt of.

571
00:45:52,200 --> 00:45:54,760
(Thunder sounds)

572
00:46:21,840 --> 00:46:25,920
I was only doing my job.

573
00:46:29,080 --> 00:46:31,120
Your job? Or you just wanted to intervene.

574
00:46:31,400 --> 00:46:33,120
I don’t want to hurt anyone.

575
00:46:33,560 --> 00:46:35,640
I just want to get what is mine back.

576
00:46:35,640 --> 00:46:38,000
(Thunder sounds)

577
00:46:57,640 --> 00:46:59,920
You already know what you’ve always wanted to know.

578
00:47:00,000 --> 00:47:01,240
Why are you still after me?

579
00:47:01,240 --> 00:47:04,920
But that’s not everything that I want to know.

580
00:47:08,600 --> 00:47:09,720
Tharn.

581
00:47:11,320 --> 00:47:12,360
Phaya.

582
00:47:13,200 --> 00:47:15,880
-Yai.
What on earth are you doing here?

583
00:47:16,920 --> 00:47:17,960
You doing here?

584
00:47:17,960 --> 00:47:19,040
I’m here to sort out something.

585
00:47:19,040 --> 00:47:21,040
Oh, you’ve come quite far.

586
00:47:21,040 --> 00:47:21,520
(The sound of laughter)

587
00:47:22,520 --> 00:47:23,520
How did he get here?

588
00:47:23,840 --> 00:47:25,040
I don’t know.

589
00:47:25,040 --> 00:47:27,280
Oh, this is my girlfriend, Sand.

590
00:47:27,600 --> 00:47:29,240
Hello.

591
00:47:30,120 --> 00:47:32,280
Wow, you’ve got a beauty as your girlfriend, huh?

592
00:47:32,320 --> 00:47:34,920
Of course. A handsome guy like me only deserves the best.

593
00:47:35,040 --> 00:47:36,320
Right, honey?

594
00:47:37,480 --> 00:47:40,320
It was quite dark so I didn’t know he actually looks like this.

595
00:47:40,320 --> 00:47:42,920
(Everyone laughs)

596
00:47:45,120 --> 00:47:48,320
That was harsh, honey. I’m hurt.

597
00:47:50,040 --> 00:47:52,440
So, welcome to Nongkai.

598
00:47:52,680 --> 00:47:54,920
It’s always crowded on this day of every year.

599
00:47:55,080 --> 00:47:57,360
Once, the traffic jam went all the way to Udon Thani.

600
00:47:58,200 --> 00:48:00,880
Those people probably wanted to come witness the Naga fireballs with their own eyes.

601
00:48:01,760 --> 00:48:02,800
So,

602
00:48:02,800 --> 00:48:05,400
Are you here for the first time?

603
00:48:06,320 --> 00:48:08,160
No, this is my second time.

604
00:48:08,160 --> 00:48:09,240
I used to come here once when I was a kid.

605
00:48:09,240 --> 00:48:10,880
I see.

606
00:48:10,880 --> 00:48:14,400
If you want to come here more often, then you should get yourself a lover in Nongkai.

607
00:48:14,560 --> 00:48:16,000
Right, Tharn?

608
00:48:17,880 --> 00:48:19,480
Do you want me to recommend someone?

609
00:48:19,600 --> 00:48:22,400
My junior is still single.

610
00:48:24,320 --> 00:48:25,000
Thank you.

611
00:48:25,480 --> 00:48:29,080
Maybe Tharn, the single one...Oops! I mean...

612
00:48:29,600 --> 00:48:31,960
Tharn might want to see the Naga fireballs now.

613
00:48:31,960 --> 00:48:33,360
Let’s go find somewhere to sit.

614
00:48:33,360 --> 00:48:34,040
Okay.

615
00:48:34,040 --> 00:48:35,240
We’ll see you at the festival then.

616
00:48:35,280 --> 00:48:37,240
I’m going to eat the grilled fish at my favourite restaurant first.

617
00:48:37,240 --> 00:48:39,480
I already made a reservation. The place is packed with people from the festival today.

618
00:48:39,480 --> 00:48:40,400
See you!

619
00:48:40,400 --> 00:48:41,600
See you.

620
00:48:42,560 --> 00:48:43,440
Want some?

621
00:48:43,960 --> 00:48:45,480
- See you then.
- See you

622
00:48:45,480 --> 00:48:46,480
- Okay.
- Bye.

623
00:48:56,120 --> 00:48:57,880
Are you ready, my guide?

624
00:48:58,880 --> 00:48:59,720
Lead the way.

625
00:49:04,040 --> 00:49:08,360
(Music)

626
00:49:29,320 --> 00:49:30,480
It’s beautiful.

627
00:49:33,760 --> 00:49:34,920
It’s so crowded this year.

628
00:49:34,920 --> 00:49:35,880
Hey, the pork here is really good.

629
00:49:35,880 --> 00:49:36,680
Really?

630
00:49:38,840 --> 00:49:40,080
Can I have one, please?

631
00:49:40,080 --> 00:49:42,600
This one and this one too. The crispy pork skin too.

632
00:49:42,720 --> 00:49:43,720
Thank you.

633
00:49:44,120 --> 00:49:44,800
Let’s go.

634
00:49:44,800 --> 00:49:45,640
Thank you.

635
00:49:45,640 --> 00:49:50,480
(Fun music)

636
00:50:05,840 --> 00:50:10,440
(Fireworks sound)

637
00:50:21,040 --> 00:50:23,320
Let’s go eat something after this.

638
00:50:23,320 --> 00:50:24,080
Okay.

639
00:50:29,360 --> 00:50:30,760
Are you okay?

640
00:50:35,400 --> 00:50:36,840
Are you afraid of the Naga statue?

641
00:50:39,320 --> 00:50:39,960
No

642
00:50:42,280 --> 00:50:43,960
But you look so pale right now.

643
00:50:46,440 --> 00:50:49,080
It’s nothing. Let’s get going.

644
00:51:08,760 --> 00:51:11,120
(Fireworks sound)

645
00:51:20,680 --> 00:51:22,280
Did you see that, honey?

646
00:51:22,880 --> 00:51:23,480
Yes.

647
00:51:23,480 --> 00:51:25,040
There are lots of them this year.

648
00:51:25,040 --> 00:51:27,280
But I only saw the first one.

649
00:51:27,280 --> 00:51:28,960
Aww, why didn’t you pay more attention?

650
00:51:29,720 --> 00:51:30,520
It’s amazing.

651
00:51:35,960 --> 00:51:37,360
Look over there!

652
00:51:38,160 --> 00:51:39,040
Did you see it?

653
00:51:39,040 --> 00:51:39,720
Yes,

654
00:51:40,120 --> 00:51:40,880
Amazing.

655
00:51:43,560 --> 00:51:44,760
But not as amazing as you.

656
00:51:53,760 --> 00:51:54,280
Where?

657
00:51:54,280 --> 00:51:55,440
- Sure?
- Yeah.

658
00:51:55,440 --> 00:51:56,960
- Really?
- Yeah.

659
00:51:56,960 --> 00:51:58,000
It was huge

660
00:51:59,120 --> 00:52:00,840
Why couldn’t you see it?

661
00:52:01,440 --> 00:52:03,440
Did you see that one Tharn was talking about?

662
00:52:03,440 --> 00:52:05,600
- No.
- Did you fool me?

663
00:52:05,600 --> 00:52:06,840
We both saw it.

664
00:52:06,880 --> 00:52:08,040
Sure?

665
00:52:09,560 --> 00:52:11,400
Yes. See that?

666
00:52:21,240 --> 00:52:23,000
Phaya, did you see it? Over there.

667
00:52:24,280 --> 00:52:25,240
Yes.

668
00:52:32,160 --> 00:52:33,320
Right in front of me

669
00:52:42,240 --> 00:52:43,800
Saw that, honey?

670
00:52:43,800 --> 00:52:44,560
Yes.

671
00:52:44,560 --> 00:52:45,760
-Yes.
-It was big.

672
00:52:55,400 --> 00:52:56,640
Are you feeling better?

673
00:52:58,280 --> 00:52:59,200
Yeah, sort of

674
00:53:01,920 --> 00:53:03,640
But you don’t look okay at all.

675
00:53:07,920 --> 00:53:09,120
I don’t know.

676
00:53:10,000 --> 00:53:12,600
I couldn’t breathe all of the sudden.

677
00:53:13,120 --> 00:53:14,920
And I felt the burning pain all over my body.

678
00:53:17,600 --> 00:53:21,560
You go enjoy the festival then.

679
00:53:21,880 --> 00:53:23,040
I’ll go back to the temple first.

680
00:53:25,360 --> 00:53:27,760
It’s okay. I’ll go back with you.

681
00:53:29,720 --> 00:53:30,560
Thanks.

682
00:53:53,480 --> 00:53:56,000
You’re so beautiful.

683
00:53:57,600 --> 00:54:01,200
Once upon a time, a Naga disguise itself as a man.

684
00:54:02,120 --> 00:54:03,560
It was long before I was born.

685
00:54:05,200 --> 00:54:08,600
There is no way you can help him, Wansarut.

686
00:54:13,120 --> 00:54:13,840
(Gasping)

687
00:54:15,400 --> 00:54:16,000
(Gasping)

688
00:54:43,560 --> 00:54:45,240
Why is it that every time I got near you,

689
00:54:47,520 --> 00:54:49,160
I’d always have a bad dream?

690
00:55:31,280 --> 00:55:32,120
Phaya,

691
00:55:32,320 --> 00:55:34,720
Sand and I will give you a tour in Nongkai today.

692
00:55:34,920 --> 00:55:36,040
Think of it as my apology

693
00:55:36,280 --> 00:55:38,080
For last nigt.

694
00:55:38,080 --> 00:55:41,080
It was too crowded. I couldn’t find you guys so I just stayed with my girlfriend.

695
00:55:42,360 --> 00:55:44,200
If you’re going to give him a tour,

696
00:55:44,560 --> 00:55:45,960
why do I have to tag along?

697
00:55:46,040 --> 00:55:47,640
I’m want to stay at the temple to take care of the Abbot.

698
00:55:47,760 --> 00:55:48,800
Ouch!….

699
00:55:48,800 --> 00:55:50,480
He wouldn’t want you to stay.

700
00:55:50,520 --> 00:55:52,200
Otherwise, why would he tell me to take you with me too?

701
00:55:53,480 --> 00:55:55,520
I’m going to take you to the cave.

702
00:55:56,360 --> 00:55:57,360
What cave?

703
00:55:58,120 --> 00:56:01,320
I’m sure you’ll like it.

704
00:56:01,560 --> 00:56:05,320
It’s said that this cave is the gateway to the city of Naga.

705
00:56:05,640 --> 00:56:11,600
There are lots of stalactites and stalagmites in the cave. It would surely give you a creep.

706
00:56:11,840 --> 00:56:14,400
I’m having goosebumps right now thinking about last night.

707
00:56:21,160 --> 00:56:22,840
Why didn’t you want to tag along with us?

708
00:56:24,320 --> 00:56:27,040
Or do you still want to sleep at the pavillion?

709
00:56:27,040 --> 00:56:27,640
Ouch!….

710
00:56:28,280 --> 00:56:29,720
Watch your mouth. We’re at the temple.

711
00:56:30,160 --> 00:56:31,960
Watch my mouth?

712
00:57:06,800 --> 00:57:07,520
Tharn

713
00:57:09,800 --> 00:57:11,080
I have to thank you though.

714
00:57:13,480 --> 00:57:15,160
If you hadn’t saved me on that day,

715
00:57:17,560 --> 00:57:18,760
I would have been dead.

716
00:57:22,960 --> 00:57:24,400
It was a good thing.

717
00:57:26,080 --> 00:57:27,720
That I got drowned?

718
00:57:28,720 --> 00:57:30,560
If I hadn’t saved your life back then,

719
00:57:31,240 --> 00:57:33,120
we wouldn’t have met like this.

720
00:57:35,720 --> 00:57:38,120
Are you trying to hit on me?

721
00:57:40,160 --> 00:57:41,120
Let’s go.

722
00:57:41,400 --> 00:57:42,840
I’ll take you to some other places.

723
00:57:45,160 --> 00:57:46,000
Where?

724
00:57:56,000 --> 00:58:00,520
[Wat PhraThat Bung Puan]
Nong Khai Province

725
00:58:00,520 --> 00:58:03,920
(Fun music)

726
00:58:04,360 --> 00:58:05,080
Let's go

727
00:58:06,840 --> 00:58:14,400
(Fun music)

728
00:58:54,680 --> 00:58:56,120
[Wat Tham Din Phiang]
Nong Khai Province

729
00:58:56,120 --> 00:58:59,280
I think there are numerous photographs of me.
Take pictures of the Buddha there.

730
00:58:59,880 --> 00:59:00,640
Here we are.

731
00:59:01,080 --> 00:59:02,320
We got here

732
00:59:02,520 --> 00:59:04,120
The Dinphiang Cave (aka Srimongkol Cave).

733
00:59:05,280 --> 00:59:09,480
The local people believe that this is the path where the Naga’s daughter has to pass through.

734
00:59:09,480 --> 00:59:12,920
One day, she fell in love with the human prince.

735
00:59:12,920 --> 00:59:14,880
But on the End of Buddhist Lent Day,

736
00:59:14,880 --> 00:59:17,280
She must go back to the Naga city.

737
00:59:17,280 --> 00:59:20,280
However, the prince had secretly followed her back.

738
00:59:20,280 --> 00:59:24,280
And finally found out that the woman he loved was a Naga.

739
00:59:24,480 --> 00:59:25,840
The prince couldn’t bare with this truth.

740
00:59:26,040 --> 00:59:28,120
So, he decided to leave her forever.

741
00:59:28,120 --> 00:59:32,600
(Music)

742
00:59:33,920 --> 00:59:34,720
Phaya

743
00:59:35,720 --> 00:59:38,000
This is where the people here believe to be the coffin of Indra Naga or the King of Naga.

744
00:59:38,520 --> 00:59:41,640
It is the coffin of Pu Innakarat.

745
00:59:48,880 --> 00:59:49,840
They believe that these poles help support the city of Naga.

746
00:59:49,840 --> 00:59:54,040
They were the pillars of the Thousand Halls that sustained the undersea city.

747
00:59:59,840 --> 01:00:00,760
They look amazing.

748
01:00:03,400 --> 01:00:04,400
Incredible.

749
01:00:06,840 --> 01:00:08,280
There’s more. Let’s go.

750
01:00:08,480 --> 01:00:09,720
- Is there anything else?
- There is more to come.

751
01:00:15,680 --> 01:00:17,120
Do you like it?

752
01:00:17,320 --> 01:00:18,120
Incredible.

753
01:00:19,920 --> 01:00:20,800
Any more places like this?

754
01:00:22,080 --> 01:00:22,960
You want to see more?

755
01:00:24,360 --> 01:00:25,440
Wait.

756
01:00:27,520 --> 01:00:28,200
What is it?

757
01:00:28,480 --> 01:00:32,520
If you want to freshen up, have it with this.

758
01:00:36,760 --> 01:00:37,560
Thanks.

759
01:00:37,760 --> 01:00:39,400
I’m going to find something to eat. So hungry right now.

760
01:00:52,520 --> 01:00:53,960
Try this and you’ll feel fresh.

761
01:01:02,400 --> 01:01:03,440
Do you think I can drink it now?

762
01:01:03,840 --> 01:01:04,760
Yeah.

763
01:01:11,400 --> 01:01:12,240
Ah, so fresh.

764
01:01:12,240 --> 01:01:13,920
Here, try it.

765
01:01:14,920 --> 01:01:16,800
Why would you put the cap on?

766
01:01:18,880 --> 01:01:19,800
By the way,

767
01:01:20,440 --> 01:01:21,920
I had a bad dream again last night.

768
01:01:23,960 --> 01:01:25,240
Again?

769
01:01:25,280 --> 01:01:26,000
Yeah.

770
01:01:28,760 --> 01:01:29,680
What was it like?

771
01:01:30,400 --> 01:01:36,200
Same old story. But this time, you were there in my dream too.

772
01:01:38,240 --> 01:01:39,800
Are you saying it was because of me

773
01:01:39,920 --> 01:01:41,000
that you had a bad dream?

774
01:01:42,240 --> 01:01:46,560
Of course, not. Forget it. Let’s go then.

775
01:01:47,880 --> 01:01:48,960
Where to, next?

776
01:01:50,400 --> 01:01:54,280
Wat Hai Sok (Nongkai province)

777
01:02:22,960 --> 01:02:25,120
Wow, is this your house?

778
01:02:25,360 --> 01:02:28,200
It looks really classy.

779
01:02:28,640 --> 01:02:31,600
I thought you said you grew up with the Abbot at the temple.

780
01:02:32,840 --> 01:02:34,600
This is my grandma’s place.

781
01:02:34,960 --> 01:02:36,960
I often come to visit her.

782
01:02:37,800 --> 01:02:42,760
Why didn’t you stay here then? The house is big. Why did you have to trouble the Abbot?

