887
01:09:09,640 --> 01:09:12,960
Come on, drink up. Stop thinking too much about it.

888
01:09:21,720 --> 01:09:24,160
- Are you serious?
- P'Yai

889
01:09:27,920 --> 01:09:32,359
Please protect your son.

890
01:09:33,080 --> 01:09:35,399
Don’t let anything bad happen to both of them.

891
01:09:36,479 --> 01:09:38,760
Don’t let what the Abbot has predicted come true.

892
01:10:07,600 --> 01:10:10,200
Hey, are you still up?

893
01:10:12,320 --> 01:10:16,520
A new hut is easier to live than an old castle.

894
01:10:18,840 --> 01:10:22,160
It’s actually ‘a happy hut is better than a gloomy castle.’

895
01:10:23,080 --> 01:10:28,800
I was just kidding. I’m thinking about something.

896
01:10:31,000 --> 01:10:32,000
About what?

897
01:10:34,920 --> 01:10:40,160
I came here because I wanted to find out more about the Naga.

898
01:10:40,880 --> 01:10:42,320
Whether it’s true or not.

899
01:10:43,520 --> 01:10:48,440
About those legends I read from the books, or even about the Naga fireballs.

900
01:10:51,280 --> 01:10:54,400
Do what you believe. Believe in what you do.
(A famous saying from the movie, ‘Mekhong Full Moon Party’)

901
01:10:55,960 --> 01:11:01,480
I watched that movie for so many times.

902
01:11:02,000 --> 01:11:04,000
And other movies about the Naga too.

903
01:11:05,440 --> 01:11:07,280
The more I kept watching them...

904
01:11:08,280 --> 01:11:12,280
the more I started to feel familiar with those stories.

905
01:11:14,240 --> 01:11:15,400
It’s really weird.

906
01:11:15,680 --> 01:11:17,200
I even dreamt about it too.

907
01:11:18,360 --> 01:11:20,520
And drew that picture in your diary.

908
01:11:20,960 --> 01:11:23,320
And believed that I were that girl you drew, right?

909
01:11:24,120 --> 01:11:33,640
It’s not like that. I just feel something every time I get near you.

910
01:11:36,800 --> 01:11:40,520
You mean, as if we’ve met long before we did at the traning camp?

911
01:11:43,080 --> 01:11:46,000
Long before you had saved my life when I was drowning.

912
01:11:47,600 --> 01:11:55,040
I feel as if we have met long before that.

913
01:11:58,680 --> 01:12:01,200
Did you use this kind of story to hit on the girls in France?

914
01:12:03,200 --> 01:12:04,520
Merci Beaucoup. (Thank you in French)

915
01:12:04,960 --> 01:12:07,040
I didn’t use it with every girl that I try to hit on.

916
01:12:07,280 --> 01:12:09,680
I only use it with someone that I really like.

917
01:12:10,280 --> 01:12:11,360
And that someone is you.

918
01:12:14,840 --> 01:12:16,240
You evil jellyfish.

919
01:12:16,640 --> 01:12:17,920
Go get some sleep.

920
01:12:29,120 --> 01:12:32,400
French people do this to say hi and goodbye.

921
01:12:34,400 --> 01:12:36,880
I got it. Can I go to sleep now?

922
01:12:50,960 --> 01:12:54,240
And this is called a ‘goodnight kiss’.

923
01:12:57,920 --> 01:12:58,840
I’m off to bed.

924
01:13:00,440 --> 01:13:01,520
(Yawning)

925
01:14:10,120 --> 01:14:11,360
(Phone buzzing)

926
01:14:12,040 --> 01:14:13,360
(Phone buzzing)

927
01:14:14,160 --> 01:14:15,120
(Phone buzzing)

928
01:14:28,440 --> 01:14:30,560
(On phone screen)
Evil Jellyfish

929
01:14:34,840 --> 01:14:37,360
If you love him, just let him know.

930
01:14:37,440 --> 01:14:39,760
Tell him how you feel.

931
01:14:40,360 --> 01:14:46,680
I don’t want those around me to be in danger.

932
01:14:48,040 --> 01:14:51,960
Geez, stop blaming yourself.

933
01:15:37,920 --> 01:15:41,600
Hey, I gave you a call so many times after we came back from Nong kai,

934
01:15:41,640 --> 01:15:43,320
why didn’t  you answer them?

935
01:15:45,040 --> 01:15:46,600
Nothing serious.

936
01:15:48,480 --> 01:15:49,520
Just too lazy to take the call.

937
01:15:53,080 --> 01:15:54,760
Are you avoiding me?

938
01:15:57,120 --> 01:15:58,840
Why would I do that?

939
01:16:04,200 --> 01:16:05,320
What the fuck?

940
01:16:07,080 --> 01:16:08,720
Hang on.

941
01:16:14,080 --> 01:16:15,320
Why are you blocking my way?

942
01:16:16,560 --> 01:16:17,800
Do you want to get hurt?

943
01:16:20,920 --> 01:16:23,280
Yes, I want to get hurt.

944
01:16:23,520 --> 01:16:24,960
I want to get hurt so badly.

945
01:16:25,640 --> 01:16:28,880
So, can you tell me now why you’re avoiding me?

946
01:16:30,200 --> 01:16:32,280
I’m not avoiding you.

947
01:16:34,160 --> 01:16:35,040
Fine.

948
01:16:36,320 --> 01:16:37,200
Let’s do this.

949
01:16:40,360 --> 01:16:42,320
Let’s have a match. If I win,

950
01:16:44,280 --> 01:16:48,560
you must admit that you’re avoiding me.

951
01:16:52,400 --> 01:16:56,160
- Okay? / - Do you really think you can beat me?

952
01:16:59,760 --> 01:17:00,840
Do you want to try?

953
01:17:02,720 --> 01:17:03,800
I’m going to kick your ass.

954
01:17:13,640 --> 01:17:15,640
- Ready? / - Bring it on.

955
01:17:51,560 --> 01:17:52,280
How does it feel?

956
01:18:16,800 --> 01:18:18,440
- Let me go!
- Do you give in now?

957
01:18:18,760 --> 01:18:19,840
I won.

958
01:18:20,600 --> 01:18:21,880
- One... / - Let me go!

959
01:18:22,440 --> 01:18:24,400
- Get off me! / - Two...

960
01:18:25,040 --> 01:18:25,920
Three...

961
01:18:26,880 --> 01:18:27,600
Four...

962
01:18:28,280 --> 01:18:29,080
Five...

963
01:18:29,760 --> 01:18:31,480
Six, Seven...

964
01:18:31,480 --> 01:18:33,720
- Eight, Nine...
- Okay, you won!

965
01:18:33,760 --> 01:18:34,560
you won!

966
01:18:38,880 --> 01:18:39,760
You lost.

967
01:18:40,600 --> 01:18:42,840
So, next time when I give you a call...

968
01:18:43,200 --> 01:18:45,120
you have to answer it. Okay?

969
01:18:46,280 --> 01:18:47,320
Bolster.

970
01:18:48,800 --> 01:18:50,840
- Got it?
- Yeah.

971
01:18:54,080 --> 01:18:55,680
You’re a good boy.

972
01:19:11,280 --> 01:19:13,480
You’ll meet the leader of Unit 1 today.

973
01:19:13,720 --> 01:19:16,320
This person will supervise the investigations under your team.

974
01:19:18,200 --> 01:19:20,320
Is it a he or a she?

975
01:19:20,960 --> 01:19:24,680
This morning, I saw that the leader of Unit 3...

976
01:19:25,080 --> 01:19:27,760
is a woman.  She looks so cool.

977
01:19:28,480 --> 01:19:30,360
You guys are considered very lucky.

978
01:19:30,400 --> 01:19:32,040
Because your team leader is very experienced.

979
01:19:32,200 --> 01:19:33,960
Never failed to arrest the criminals in every case.

980
01:19:34,360 --> 01:19:36,960
Is that why we are Unit 1?

981
01:19:37,800 --> 01:19:41,680
Yes. There he is, your team leader.

982
01:19:58,200 --> 01:19:59,800
Attention!

983
01:20:03,200 --> 01:20:04,000
Inspector.

984
01:20:07,240 --> 01:20:08,800
Nice to meet you all.

985
01:20:09,720 --> 01:20:14,160
I’m Police Major Akkanee Assawawaisoon, your team leader.

986
01:20:14,960 --> 01:20:18,480
Shit, we’re so doomed.

987
01:20:19,240 --> 01:20:24,640
You didn’t mention anything about being our team leader when we parted, Captain. I mean Inspector.

988
01:20:27,240 --> 01:20:31,640
If I had mentioned it earlier, I wouldn’t have been able to find out whether you’d be true to your words about your determination...

989
01:20:31,800 --> 01:20:34,480
when you told me on the last day of the training.

990
01:20:41,000 --> 01:20:42,920
I can still remember it word by word.

991
01:20:45,720 --> 01:20:47,440
What did I say to him?

992
01:20:48,920 --> 01:20:52,840
You gave him an earful.
Shit.

993
01:20:52,960 --> 01:20:55,680
Please keep in mind...

994
01:20:55,920 --> 01:20:57,320
that this is a real workplace.

995
01:20:57,760 --> 01:20:59,080
You’re no longer at the traning camp.

996
01:21:00,200 --> 01:21:02,400
I only have three simple rules if we’re going to work together.

997
01:21:03,040 --> 01:21:06,080
First is teamwork.

998
01:21:06,960 --> 01:21:10,600
There’ll be no solo investigation.
Or doing anything without permission or approval from others.

999
01:21:12,160 --> 01:21:16,640
Second, the supervisor’s order is considered final...

1000
01:21:17,280 --> 01:21:19,840
and cannot be challenged or disobeyed.

1001
01:21:20,240 --> 01:21:21,560
Those who do will get kicked out of the team immediately.

1002
01:21:23,000 --> 01:21:29,240
Third, never mix business with your peronsal affairs.

1003
01:21:30,720 --> 01:21:33,120
Every time that you are out on an investigation...

1004
01:21:34,120 --> 01:21:36,160
there must be no mistake.

1005
01:21:36,440 --> 01:21:41,440
Just one false step and that would mean...
you’re throwing away justice and the truth of the case.

1006
01:21:42,480 --> 01:21:44,800
- Got it? / - Hooya!

1007
01:21:45,720 --> 01:21:47,720
No need to say ‘Hooya’. This is not a training camp.

1008
01:21:48,920 --> 01:21:51,440
I hope we’d be able to work together for a long time.

1009
01:21:52,440 --> 01:21:55,120
And that no one would get kicked out soon.

1010
01:22:04,200 --> 01:22:06,600
Shit. What did I say to him back then?

1011
01:22:07,240 --> 01:22:08,720
You were giving him an earful.

1012
01:22:09,440 --> 01:22:11,520
- Geez, Yai.
- You too.

1013
01:22:11,880 --> 01:22:13,920
I can’t remember what I said to him.

1014
01:22:14,920 --> 01:22:15,920
But I’m so happy.

1015
01:22:16,960 --> 01:22:18,200
Happy my foot.

1016
01:22:18,440 --> 01:22:20,200
I’m so dead.

1017
01:22:23,320 --> 01:22:25,280
- Put all the information on the screen. / - Yes, sir.

1018
01:22:25,920 --> 01:22:26,560
Come in.

1019
01:22:27,360 --> 01:22:31,800
- Please take a seat. / - Yes, sir.

1020
01:22:48,760 --> 01:22:52,840
Inspector, the information you’ve asked for is ready.

1021
01:22:54,400 --> 01:22:55,160
Give it to the team.

1022
01:22:57,640 --> 01:23:00,800
This is Lieutenant Singh. He’s one of our team.

1023
01:23:01,080 --> 01:23:02,680
He’d help support you on the IT part.

1024
01:23:02,960 --> 01:23:04,040
Hello.

1025
01:23:04,200 --> 01:23:05,880
I’m Lieut Singh, the IT officer.

1026
01:23:06,160 --> 01:23:07,160
Pleased to work with you.

1027
01:23:07,720 --> 01:23:09,760
That one is Wit.

1028
01:23:10,320 --> 01:23:12,000
He’s the forensic officer.

1029
01:23:21,680 --> 01:23:23,120
This is your first case.

1030
01:23:24,400 --> 01:23:26,440
The rapist murder.

1031
01:23:30,560 --> 01:23:32,840
I heard about his case whileI was at the camp.

1032
01:23:33,240 --> 01:23:39,560
Both victims were charged with rape.
Their bodies were shot and hung up by the necks.
Their genitals were also cut off.
That’s what I heard.

1033
01:23:41,000 --> 01:23:44,400
That’s right. Now, we have the third victim.

1034
01:23:45,720 --> 01:23:49,120
The first victim was a 45-year-old male. The name is Ohm.

1035
01:23:49,400 --> 01:23:57,280
He was beaten up and his tongue got cut off.
We found evidence of torturing with candles. His genital was cut off.
He was charged with raping his stepchild and was released less than 2 weeks before he got killed.

1036
01:23:58,680 --> 01:24:00,280
